The Argentine Jesuit, who suffers from respiratory problems and suffered the removal of the right lobe when he was young, contracted a <a href="https://www.agi.it/scienza/news/2025-02-17/cosa-e-infection-polymicrobial-vie-respiratory-papapa-30067012/">“ polimicrobial infection
These latest news has rekindled the health concerns of the head of the Catholic Church, whose health in decline is put to a hard test by an overburdened agenda and a hectic rhythm due also to the celebrations related to the Jubilee.&nbsp;
"The information we regularly give you." Thus Vatican sources comment on the continuous and insistent fake news > circulating these days, that is, Pope Francis would already die.» "Fake news comment on themselves."
Clear all commitments. It remains only to decide for the Angelus on Sunday.
