&nbsp;
According to the same sources, the Pope is not subjected to additional oxygen administration. The Pontiff would be "self-ventilated".><br> As for visits to the tenth floor of the Gemelli, sources confirm that Francis was prescribed absolute rest. The visits he receives are only those of his collaborators who carry documents and papers to be viewed.
&nbsp;
<h2>Cei, support the Pope with prayer</h2>
&nbsp;"We renew the closeness of the Churches in Italy to Pope Francis, admitted from Friday 14 February to the Policlinico A. Gemelli. In entrusting to the Lord the work of doctors and health personnel, we tighten to the Holy Father with affection, inviting ecclesial communities to support him with prayer at this time of suffering." This is what the Presidency of the Council says.
<h2> The text of General Audience
A catechesis dedicated to the childhood of Jesus, to the visit of the three Magi. The text of the General Audience was widespread - then cancelled for the reconstruction of the Gemini - that Pope Francis should hold today.> The Magi, underlines the Pontiff in the text, "do not belong to the people of the covenant". And if the pastors of Bethlehem had spoken in the previous catechesis, "marginated in Jewish society because they considered 'impuries'", the Gospels, with the arrival of the Magi, "> tell us therefore clearly that the poor and foreigners are invited among the first to meet the God made child, the Saviour of the world".
"The Magi thus become the first believers among all the pagans, the image of the Church united by every language and nation," says Bergoglio, who also wants to reflect on the behavior of the scribes, who know the Scriptures, asked by Herod to know where the leader and pastor of the people of Israel would be born. "For those who are attached to power, Jesus is not the hope to welcome, but a threat to be eliminated!"
"However the scribes, who know how to spot exactly the birthplace of the Messiah, indicate the way to others but themselves do not move! It is not enough, in fact - the Pope observes in catechesis -, to know the prophetic texts in order to tune with the divine frequencies, it is necessary to let oneself dig inside and to allow the Word of God to revive the analyte in search, to increase the desire to see God". The Pontiff concludes his catechesis by exhorting to be like the Magi, "pilgrins of hope" > who, with great courage, have turned their steps, their hearts and their goods towards Him who is hope not only of Israel but of all peoples". "We strive to worship God in his smallness, in his royalty that does not crush but makes free and able to serve with dignity. And we offer him the most beautiful gifts, to express our faith and our love." &nbsp;
